Fastly conflict detector script Last month, I built a CI solution for our project and adding a conflict detector to our build commands. This script runned so slow because it will check all application files (and our application codebase has many of css, js files).
This was the script
#!/bin/bash grep -rli --exclude=conflict_detector.sh --exclude-dir={.git,vendor,node_modules} &quot;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; HEAD&quot; . if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then exit 1 else exit 0 fi  Today, I think why don&rsquo;t we just check recently updated files (in the latest commit) ?

